00167 /* Be sure they don't exist, since we don't want to use them outside of checks
00168  * and so we want the compile failure.
00169  */
00170 #define DECLARE_DBUS_NAME_CHECK(what)
00171 #define DEFINE_DBUS_NAME_CHECK(what)
00172 
00173 #else /* !DBUS_DISABLE_CHECKS */
00174 
00178 #define DECLARE_DBUS_NAME_CHECK(what) \
00179 dbus_bool_t _dbus_check_is_valid_##what (const char *name)
00180 
00183 #define DEFINE_DBUS_NAME_CHECK(what)                                    \
00184 dbus_bool_t                                                             \
00185 _dbus_check_is_valid_##what (const char *name)                          \
00186 {                                                                       \
00187   DBusString str;                                                       \
00188                                                                         \
00189   if (name == NULL)                                                     \
00190     return FALSE;                                                       \
00191                                                                         \
00192   _dbus_string_init_const (&str, name);                                 \
00193   return _dbus_validate_##what (&str, 0,                                \
00194                                 _dbus_string_get_length (&str));        \
00195 }
00196 #endif /* !DBUS_DISABLE_CHECKS */
